curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/12359' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3699", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM3699 is a bidirectional, quad, SPDT (single-  pole/double-throw), TTL/CMOS compatible analog switch.  It operates from a 1.8V to 4.35V single power supply.  The SGM3699 features low on-resistance, low voltage  and fast switching times. The high performances make  it very suitable for multiple applications, such as  portable equipment, audio and video signal routing, etc.  In addition, the SGM3699 can be used as a dual 2-to-1  multiplexer/demultiplexer because it has two logic  control inputs. Low power consumption is also one of  the important reasons that make it a good choice.  The SGM3699 is available in Green TQFN-3×3-16L  package. It operates over an ambient temperature  range of -40℃ to +85℃.  "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/12360' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM3699", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Single Supply Voltage Range: 1.8V to 4.35V  ● -3dB Bandwidth: 70MHz  ● Fast Switching Times (V+ = 4.2V):  tON: 52ns  tOFF: 25ns  ● Low On-Resistance: 0.5Ω (TYP)  ● Low On-Resistance Flatness  ● Low Power Consumption  ● High Off-Isolation: -75dB at 1MHz  ● Low Crosstalk: -100dB at 1MHz  ● TTL/CMOS Compatible  ● Rail-to-Rail Input and Output Operation  ● -40℃ to +85℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in Green TQFN-3×3-16L Package      "}'
